</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1793,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,1794,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="279">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[304,429,1793,1820]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,452,1585]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1391,450,1586]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Versicolora ziyongi sp. nov., holotype, male. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view; C. head and thorax, dorsal view; D. head and thorax, ventral view; E. abdomen, ventral view; F. male pygofer, ventral view G. male pygofer, lateral view; H. left fore leg, showing the spines on femur. aed, aedeagus; as, anal style; db, dorsal beak; lul, lateral uncus lobe; mul, median uncus lobe; upl, upper lobe of pygofer." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3737509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3737509/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="279">Fig. 1A, C</figureCitation>
). Pronotum almost green, with pair of central black fasciae extending from anterior margin to posterior end and irregular black spots near lateral fissures and paramedian fissures; pronotal collar reddish brown, with pair of black spots on posterolateral area, posterior margin rippled. Mesonotum mostly green, covered with silvery hair; with curved black fascia surrounding each submedian sigilla and longitudinal black fascia along each lateral sigilla. Cruciform elevation reddish brown, with black spots centrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1793,2036]" pageId="2" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,1974,2000]" pageId="2" pageNumber="279">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[269,391,1973,2000]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1614,1639]" captionTargetBox="[196,1389,452,1585]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[195,1391,450,1586]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Versicolora ziyongi sp. nov., holotype, male. A. habitus, dorsal view; B. habitus, ventral view; C. head and thorax, dorsal view; D. head and thorax, ventral view; E. abdomen, ventral view; F. male pygofer, ventral view G. male pygofer, lateral view; H. left fore leg, showing the spines on femur. aed, aedeagus; as, anal style; db, dorsal beak; lul, lateral uncus lobe; mul, median uncus lobe; upl, upper lobe of pygofer." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3737509" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3737509/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="279">Fig. 1D, H</figureCitation>
